To fix this issue, you can try initializing the arrays inside the constructor of your `SudokuBoard` class. For example:
```java
public SudokuBoard(int[][] init) {
    board = new int[9][9]; // initialize the board array
    availableNumbers = new int[9]; // initialize the available numbers array
    fixedSquares = new int[9][9]; // initialize the fixed squares array

    for (int i = 0; i < init.length; i++) {
        for (int j = 0; j < init[i].length; j++) {
            board[i][j] = init[i][j]; // set the values of the board array
        }
    }
}
```
This will ensure that all arrays are initialized and can be accessed without causing a `NullPointerException`.

